{"word":"βίος","slug":"βίος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>βίος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> vivus] ‘life’<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘state of being alive’, <b><i>life</i> <a href='B:490 8:14'>Lk 8:14</a>; <a href='B:610 2:2'>1 Ti 2:2</a>; <a href='B:620 2:4'>2 Ti 2:4</a>; <a href='B:670 4:3'>1 Pt 4:3</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘circumstance(s) connected with conducting one’s life or maintaining it’, <b><i>livelihood, (means of) living</i> <a href='B:480 12:44'>Mk 12:44</a>; <a href='B:490 8:43'>Lk 8:43</a>; <a href='B:490 15:12'>15:12</a>, <a href='B:490 15:30'>30</a>; <a href='B:490 21:4'>21:4</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>β. τοῦ ϰόσμου</el> <i>worldly goods</i> <b><a href='B:690 3:17'>1 J 3:17</a>;</b> of haughty consumerism <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀλαζονεία\">ἀλαζονεία</a> τοῦ β.</el> <b><a href='B:690 2:16'>1 J 2:16</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Βιθυνία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:βιόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}